PATENT CLAIMS

The following inventions and methods are claimed as intellectual property of 
AverNova LLC and may be subject to patent protection:

CLAIM 1: CONDITIONAL ACTION GENERATION SYSTEM FOR UTILITY OPERATIONS
A computer-implemented method for automatically generating operational actions 
based on AI analysis thresholds, comprising:
   a) Receiving analysis results from specialized AI agents regarding utility 
      infrastructure conditions;
   b) Evaluating said results against configurable threshold values;
   c) Conditionally generating one or more action types including alerts, work 
      orders, scheduled maintenance, asset status updates, event logs, and 
      notifications based on threshold evaluation;
   d) Wherein different action types are triggered at different threshold 
      levels, enabling graduated response to infrastructure conditions.

CLAIM 2: MULTI-AGENT ORCHESTRATION SYSTEM FOR UTILITY PLANNING
A system and method for coordinating multiple specialized AI agents for 
utility infrastructure analysis, comprising:
   a) A supervisor agent that receives natural language queries regarding 
      utility operations;
   b) Query analysis to determine appropriate routing to one or more 
      specialized domain agents;
   c) Specialized agents including but not limited to: storm resilience 
      analysis, load forecasting, grid topology tracing, and capacity checking;
   d) Aggregation and presentation of multi-agent results through a unified 
      interface.

CLAIM 3: HUMAN-IN-THE-LOOP APPROVAL WORKFLOW WITH METRICS FEEDBACK
A method for managing AI agent decision execution with human oversight, 
comprising:
   a) Intercepting agent-proposed actions based on trust level classification;
   b) Queuing said actions for human review in a pending approvals interface;
   c) Recording human approval or rejection decisions;
   d) Automatically updating agent performance metrics including decision 
      count, success rate, and trust score based on approval outcomes;
   e) Using updated metrics to inform future autonomy level progression.

CLAIM 4: DOMAIN-SPECIFIC AI AGENTS FOR UTILITY INFRASTRUCTURE ANALYSIS
Specialized AI agent implementations for utility planning operations, including:
   a) Storm Resilience Agent: Analyzing weather event impacts, outage risks, 
      vegetation management, and emergency preparedness;
   b) Load Forecast Agent: Projecting demand growth, analyzing consumption 
      patterns, and forecasting infrastructure requirements;
   c) Grid Topology Agent: Performing network traces, connectivity analysis, 
      and power flow verification;
   d) Capacity Check Agent: Evaluating headroom availability, connection 
      feasibility, and upgrade requirements for new loads.

CLAIM 5: ADAPTIVE CARD RENDERING FOR UTILITY DATA VISUALIZATION
A method for presenting utility infrastructure analysis through adaptive card 
interfaces, comprising:
   a) Dynamic card generation based on agent response type and content;
   b) Structured data presentation with expandable sections for detailed 
      analysis;
   c) Embedded action buttons for workflow initiation directly from analysis 
      results;
   d) Real-time status indicators for infrastructure components.

